'''Ernst Mengin''' (16 June 1893 – 5 January 1973) was a [[Germany|German]] [[Mesoamerica]]nist. He studied under [[Walter Lehmann (scholar)|Walter Lehmann]] and [[Konrad Theodor Preuss]], who in turn had studied under [[Eduard Seler]]. In 1934 Mengin and his family moved from [[Berlin]] to [[Copenhagen]], [[Denmark]], and he delivered lectures at the [[University of Copenhagen]].

