'''Sverre Hartmann''' (2 May 1917 &ndash; 22 September 2003) was a Norwegian historian and jurist. He was born in Borgund.  His research interests primarily focused on Norway during [[World War II]]. Among his books are ''Spillet on Norge'' from 1958 and ''Fører uten folk'' from 1959.
